@* Decision 138's BOUNDARY. Validation is a subsystem, not a component mapping: EditContext, field
   state, message stores and the DataAnnotations rules themselves. Without validators every submit IS
   valid (Blazor's own behaviour), so OnValidSubmit fires on every submit and there is nothing to emit
   for validity. Ignoring a validator would let an invalid model submit SILENTLY -- the wrong answer
   dressed as the right one -- so it is refused. *@
<EditForm Model="@model"><DataAnnotationsValidator /><button id="s" type="submit">s</button></EditForm>

@code {
    private Person model = new Person();
    public record Person { public string Name { get; set; } = ""; }
}
